  <span class="04_bp_blueHead">Gartner Best Practices Groups (BPGs)</span>
are structured forums where business managers, IT managers and senior staff share business and technology experiences and learnings under the professional guidance of Gartner.<p />

Peer groups collaborate to brainstorm, solve problems and improve performance. The unique combination of practical peer experience and Gartner analyst expertise shortens the learning curve, saving costly errors. Gartner Best Practices Groups have been established in a variety of subject areas from system assist processor (SAP), to World Class Customer Service, and Outsourcing to Information Security Management. 
